# service-categories-model

The service categories model implements three primary service types with associated billing rules:

## Service Categories

1. Travel Services
- PT (Personal Transport)
- FS-OH (Family Support - Office Hours) 
- FS-IH (Family Support - In Home)
- Each includes mileage tracking at $0.67/mile

2. Drug Testing Services
- 5 distinct billing codes (specific codes not detailed in spec)
- Specialized billing rules for each test type

3. Case Management/Intake
- Assessment services
- Standard case management tracking

## Business Rules

### Time Calculations
- Automatic transport hours calculation by service type
- Billable hours computation for face-to-face services
- Indirect hours tracking for FS-OH and FS-IH categories

### Service Entry Structure
- Hierarchical system with main/sub-entries
- Required fields: service type, client, staff
- Specialized handling for complex service visits

### Financial Rules
- Mileage reimbursement at fixed rate ($0.67/mile)
- Service hour categorization:
  * Billable service time
  * Transport time
  * Indirect service hours

Importance Score: 85/100
- Core business model defining service categorization
- Critical billing and time calculation rules
- Essential for financial operations and compliance

